IN 1940S NEW YORK, CUSTODIANS AND THEIR FAMILIES OFTEN LIVED IN LIBRARIES.
RONALD CLARK LIVED ON THE TOP FLOOR WITH HIS FAMILY.
HE THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH, BUT HIS FATHER TOLD HIM THEY WERE ACTUALLY POOR.
HIS FATHER WOULD WAX THE TOPS OF BOOKSHELVES AND WHEN YOU LOOKED FROM UPSTAIRS THEY SHONE.
CLARK WAS A BIT ASHAMED OF THE FACT THAT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY AROUND OTHER KIDS.
EVEN THOUGH HE DIDN'T HAVE FRIENDS OVER HE WOULD READ ALL THROUGH THE NIGHT.
IF IT WASN'T FOR LIVING IN A LIBRARY HE WOULDN'T HAVE HAD THE DRIVE TO LEARN AT ALL.
HE WAS THE FIRST ONE IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL.
MORE THAN THAT, HE WAS THE FIRST ONE TO ATTEND COLLEGE.
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE AND SHOWED HIS FATHER HIS OFFICE.
HIS FATHER WAS A QUIET PERSON BUT WAS PROUD OF HIS SON AND WANTED HIM TO SUCCEED IN LIFE.
AT THE END OF THE DAY, PROFESSOR CLARK WAS PROUD OF THE FACT THAT HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY AND THINKS THAT IT WAS VERY IMPORTANT TO HIS CAREER PATH AND LIFE.
THE VIDEO WAS CALLED THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
IF RONALD HAD ANY QUESTIONS IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT AS A CHILD, HE WOULD JUST GO DOWNSTAIRS AND READ ALL NIGHT.

IN THE 1940S IN NEW YORK, CUSTODIANS SOMETIMES LIVED IN LIBRARIES.
RONALD LIVED WITH HIS MOM AND DAD ON THE TOP FLOOR OF A LIBRARY.
RONALD THOUGHT THEY WERE RICH BUT HIS FATHER TOLD HIM THEY WERE ACTUALLY POOR.
HIS DAD HAD TO CLEAN UP CHEWING GUM AND DUST, AND HE WOULD POLISH THE TOPS OF BOOKSHELVES.
WHEN YOU LOOKED AT THE BOOKSHELVES FROM UPSTAIRS THEY WOULD SHINE.
RONALD WOULD STAY UP UNTIL 3 AM SOMETIMES READING BOOKS.
THE LIBRARY MADE HIM WANT TO START LEARNING AND FINISH HIGH SCHOOL.
HE WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO FINISH HIGH SCHOOL AND ATTEND COLLEGE.
HE BECAME A PROFESSOR AND SHOWED HIS FATHER HIS OFFICE, AND HE WAS QUIET IN RESPONSE, BUT PROUD.
HIS DAD WANTED HIM TO DO WELL IN LIFE.
HE IS GLAD THAT HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY, BECAUSE HE WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN SO INTERESTED IN LEARNING IF HE HAD BEEN IN ANOTHER LIVING SITUATION.
HE WAS SPEAKING WITH HIS DAUGHTER DURING THE INTERVIEW.
THE VIDEO WAS CALLED THE TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE.
